description.narrative: The objectives of the Project are to assist the Borrower to resume the delivery of education services in primary schools, which implies: (i) providing quality school inputs to guarantee teaching and learning in classrooms, and (ii) improving access to education and retention of primary school children.

condition.narrative: Acquire, by not later than September 30 of each year, a stock of textbooks and pedagogical guides in adequate numbers for basicsubject matters.
Deposit into the Project Account for the counterpart funds, on the first day of each quarter, an amount equivalent to CFAF500,000,000.
Re-establish, no later than October 1, 2008, the Education and Training Sector Inter-ministerial Committee. (CICSE)
The Borrower shall by October 31 of each year, prepare draft work plans and related budgets and submit them to the Association.
The Borrower shall update the Procurement Plan and furnish such update to the Association not later than 12 months after the dateof the preceding Procurement Plan.
The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements periodically audited by independent auditors.
The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association not later than 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter, interimun-audited financial reports
